{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nMutation testing currently covers only five behavioral cores (signing, gates,\nnext-batch, validate, reducer processors) per `docs/mutation-testing.md`; the concurrency\nmachinery the other stories harden — sync branch selection, compaction fold/rollback\ndecisions, push policy/retry classification, lock stale-owner/reclamation — has no\nmutation evidence. Once behavioral tests for those paths exist (S1, S3, S4), narrow\nmutation shards over their pure decision logic will confirm the new assertions actually\nkill mutants rather than just raising line coverage.\n\n## What\n\n- Extract small pure decision helpers where needed and add narrow mutation-testing\n  shards for them, rather than mutating whole subprocess-heavy orchestration modules.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `docs/mutation-testing.md` (shard config / `only_mutate` additions)\n- Small helper extractions in `src/rebar/_store/{sync,push,lock}.py` and\n  `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` decision logic, if needed for tractable mutation.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Mutation shards target the paths that have behavioral tests once their prerequisite\n      stories land: compaction fold/rollback (S1), remote-append (S4), push (S3). Sync\n      branch selection and lock stale-owner/reclamation are only sharded if this story\n      also adds their behavioral tests; otherwise they are explicitly DESCOPED here and\n      noted as requiring a follow-up story before mutation shards are meaningful.\n- [ ] Shards target pure/near-pure helpers (extracted if necessary) — not whole\n      subprocess-heavy modules — to avoid no-test attribution and equivalent-mutant noise.\n- [ ] Mapped scores for the new shards are recorded in `docs/mutation-testing.md`.\n- [ ] This story is scheduled AFTER S1/S3/S4 land (documented as depends_on).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783887516571283001,"uuid":"00b12c69-5901-4624-ae6f-befa41c9b760"}